            <title>[LU-13961] kernel update [RHEL8.2 4.18.0-193.19.1.el8_2]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13961</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Bug Fixes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;FJ8.2 Bug&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;REG&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; memory-hotplug: Memory hot-adding fails (BZ#1854207)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;nftables segfault on working with non-empty interval sets using rhel-8.1 kernel (BZ#1854531)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RHEL8.2 - s390: prevent leaking kernel address in BEAR (KASLR) (BZ#1854986)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;kernel-debug&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; UBSAN: Undefined behaviour in drivers/iommu/arm-smmu.c and iommu.c (BZ#1856966)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Update nvme driver with one patch (BZ#1857115)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;NVMeoF RDMA OPA: kmemleak observer after reset_controller operation (BZ#1857757)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;iwlwifi 9462 and 9560 init fixes (BZ#1857773)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;PANIC&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;KVM guests PANIC during install with AMD milan host (BZ#1857796)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;zfcp: Fix panic on ERP timeout for previously dismissed ERP (BZ#1861355)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;High iSCSI read latency resolved by &apos;tcp: implement coalescing on backlog queue&apos; (BZ#1861378)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Backport patch for reading SELinux labels before policy load (BZ#1861721)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Backport patch for SELinux labeling before policy load (BZ#1861722)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


